cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CE, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a systematic design of space-time block codes (STBC) which can achieve high rate and full diversity. Information theory deals with the fundamental limits of communication and coding, which is relevant to the proposed STBC design. 
2. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper discusses encoding and decoding techniques for STBC, which is a signal processing problem. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - STBC is used in wireless communication systems, which is a networking problem. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper discusses the decoding complexity of the proposed STBC, which is a computational problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - STBC is used in multimedia communication systems, which is relevant to this paper.
